1
00:00:41,708 --> 00:00:45,420
For more than a year, ominous
rumours had been circulating...

2
00:00:45,545 --> 00:00:47,839
...among high-level
Western leaders...

3
00:00:47,965 --> 00:00:51,843
...that the Soviet Union had been at
work on what was hinted to be...

4
00:00:51,969 --> 00:00:55,639
...the ultimate weapon:
a doomsday device.

5
00:00:55,764 --> 00:00:59,601
Intelligence sources traced the site
of the top-secret Russian project...

6
00:00:59,726 --> 00:01:02,354
...to the perpetually fog-shrouded
wasteland...

7
00:01:02,479 --> 00:01:05,816
...below the Arctic peaks
of the Zhokhov Islands.

8
00:01:05,941 --> 00:01:07,317
What they were building...

9
00:01:07,442 --> 00:01:11,196
...or why it should be located in such
a remote and desolate place...

10
00:01:11,321 --> 00:01:13,657
...no one could say.

11
00:03:43,890 --> 00:03:47,310
-General Ripper, sir.
-Group Captain Mandrake speaking.

12
00:03:47,728 --> 00:03:50,480
-This is General Ripper speaking.
-Yes, sir.

13
00:03:50,605 --> 00:03:54,359
-Do you recognise my voice?
-I do, sir. Why do you ask?

14
00:03:54,484 --> 00:03:56,194
Why do you think I ask?

15
00:03:56,361 --> 00:03:59,865
Well, I don't know, sir. We spoke
just a few moments ago, didn't we?

16
00:03:59,990 --> 00:04:05,203
You don't think I'd ask unless it was
pretty damned important, do you?

17
00:04:05,328 --> 00:04:09,040
-No, I don't, sir, no.
-Let's see if we can stay on the ball.

18
00:04:09,666 --> 00:04:12,502
Has the wing confirmed holding
at their fail-safe points?

19
00:04:12,627 --> 00:04:15,380
Yes, sir. The confirmations
have all just come in.

20
00:04:15,505 --> 00:04:18,967
Very well.
Now, listen to me carefully.

21
00:04:19,092 --> 00:04:21,678
The base is being
put on condition red.

22
00:04:21,803 --> 00:04:24,306
I want this flashed
to all sections immediately.

23
00:04:24,431 --> 00:04:27,684
Condition red. Jolly good idea.
Keeps the men on their toes.

24
00:04:27,809 --> 00:04:30,020
I'm afraid this is not an exercise.

25
00:04:31,313 --> 00:04:32,981
Not an exercise, sir?

26
00:04:34,357 --> 00:04:39,196
I shouldn't tell you this, but you're a
good officer and have a right to know.

27
00:04:39,321 --> 00:04:41,323
It looks like
we're in a shooting war.

28
00:04:42,115 --> 00:04:44,075
Oh, hell.

29
00:04:44,201 --> 00:04:47,245
-Are the Russians involved?
-That's all I've been told.

30
00:04:47,412 --> 00:04:52,209
It came in on the red phone. I'm gonna
follow orders and seal this base tight.

31
00:04:52,918 --> 00:04:56,755
Now, I want you to
transmit Plan R...

32
00:04:56,880 --> 00:04:58,757
...R for Robert, to the wing.

33
00:04:58,882 --> 00:05:02,219
-Plan R for Robert.
-Is it that bad, sir?

34
00:05:02,344 --> 00:05:04,763
-Looks like it's pretty hairy.
-Yes, sir.

35
00:05:04,930 --> 00:05:06,890
Plan R for Robert, sir.

36
00:05:07,015 --> 00:05:10,268
Now, last, and possibly
most important...

37
00:05:10,435 --> 00:05:14,397
...I want all privately-owned radios
to be immediately impounded.

38
00:05:14,523 --> 00:05:18,235
They might be used to issue
instructions to saboteurs.

39
00:05:18,360 --> 00:05:21,780
As I previously arranged, Air Police
will have lists of all owners.

40
00:05:21,905 --> 00:05:25,617
I want every single one of them
collected without exception.

41
00:05:25,742 --> 00:05:28,078
After you've done that,
report back to me.

42
00:05:55,105 --> 00:05:57,774
In order to guard against
surprise nuclear attack...

43
00:05:57,899 --> 00:05:59,818
...America's
Strategic Air Command...

44
00:05:59,985 --> 00:06:02,779
...maintains a large force
of B-52 bombers...

45
00:06:02,904 --> 00:06:05,448
...airborne 24 hours a day.

46
00:06:05,782 --> 00:06:10,453
Each B-52 can deliver a nuclear
bomb load of 50 megatonnes...

47
00:06:10,871 --> 00:06:16,167
...equal to 16 times the total explosive
force of all the bombs and shells...

48
00:06:16,209 --> 00:06:20,005
...used by all the armies
in World War II.

49
00:06:20,130 --> 00:06:22,799
Based in America,
the Airborne Alert Force...

50
00:06:22,924 --> 00:06:25,927
...Is deployed from the Persian Gulf
to the Arctic Ocean.

51
00:06:26,052 --> 00:06:29,139
But they have one geographical factor
in common:

52
00:06:29,264 --> 00:06:33,184
They are all two hours
from their targets inside Russia.

53
00:07:53,014 --> 00:07:56,017
Major Kong, I know you'll think
this is crazy...

54
00:07:56,142 --> 00:07:59,771
...but I just got a message from base
over the CRM 114.

55
00:08:00,855 --> 00:08:04,859
It decodes as wing attack Plan R.
R for Romeo.

56
00:08:07,904 --> 00:08:12,158
Goldie, did you say
wing attack Plan R?

57
00:08:12,492 --> 00:08:13,910
Yes, sir, I have.

58
00:08:17,580 --> 00:08:20,750
Goldie, how many times have
I told you guys...

59
00:08:20,875 --> 00:08:23,920
...that I don't want
no horsing around on the airplane?

60
00:08:24,045 --> 00:08:26,756
I'm not horsing around, sir,
that's how it decodes.

61
00:08:26,881 --> 00:08:30,135
Well, I've been to one world fair,
a picnic and a rodeo...

62
00:08:30,176 --> 00:08:33,430
...and that's the stupidest thing
I ever heard over earphones.

63
00:08:33,555 --> 00:08:35,432
You sure you got today's code?

64
00:08:36,891 --> 00:08:37,976
Yes, sir, it is.

65
00:08:38,101 --> 00:08:40,603
There's just gotta be
something wrong.

66
00:08:40,729 --> 00:08:43,106
Wait a second, I'm coming back.

67
00:09:17,307 --> 00:09:20,935
Maybe you'd better get
a confirmation from base.

68
00:09:21,060 --> 00:09:22,729
Yes, sir.

69
00:09:43,583 --> 00:09:47,045
Major Kong, is it possible
this is some kind of loyalty test?

70
00:09:47,212 --> 00:09:50,173
Give the go code and then recall
to see who would actually go?

71
00:09:50,715 --> 00:09:54,344
Ain't nobody ever got
the go code yet.

72
00:09:54,469 --> 00:09:56,638
Old Ripper wouldn't be giving us
Plan R...

73
00:09:56,763 --> 00:09:59,390
...unless them Russkies had
clobbered Washington...

74
00:09:59,516 --> 00:10:02,018
...and a lot of other towns
with a sneak attack.

75
00:10:02,143 --> 00:10:03,228
Yes, sir.

76
00:10:03,353 --> 00:10:05,855
Major Kong, message
from base confirmed.

77
00:10:10,485 --> 00:10:13,571
Well, boys, I reckon this is it.

78
00:10:13,863 --> 00:10:17,659
Nuclear combat toe-to-toe
with the Russkies.

79
00:10:32,465 --> 00:10:37,387
Now, look, boys, I ain't much
of a hand at making speeches.

80
00:10:38,388 --> 00:10:42,016
But I got a pretty fair idea
that something doggone important...

81
00:10:42,141 --> 00:10:43,768
...Is going on back there.

82
00:10:43,893 --> 00:10:48,606
Now, I've got a fair idea of the kind
of personal emotions...

83
00:10:48,731 --> 00:10:51,276
...that some of you fellows
may be thinking.

84
00:10:51,401 --> 00:10:54,404
Heck, I reckon you wouldn't even be
human beings...

85
00:10:54,571 --> 00:10:59,075
...If you didn't have strong personal
feelings about nuclear combat.

86
00:10:59,492 --> 00:11:01,744
But I want you to remember
one thing:

87
00:11:01,870 --> 00:11:04,581
That folks back home
is counting on you...

88
00:11:04,706 --> 00:11:07,250
...and by golly,
we ain't about to let them down.

89
00:11:08,334 --> 00:11:10,712
Tell you something else.

90
00:11:11,546 --> 00:11:16,217
If this thing turns out to be half as
important as I figure it just might be...

91
00:11:16,342 --> 00:11:20,805
...I'd say that you're all in line
for some important promotions...

92
00:11:20,930 --> 00:11:24,100
...and personal citations
when this thing's over with.

93
00:11:24,225 --> 00:11:27,145
And that goes for
every last one of you...

94
00:11:27,270 --> 00:11:30,940
...regardless of your race,
colour or your creed.

95
00:11:31,065 --> 00:11:34,777
Now, let's get this thing on the hump.
We got some flying to do.

96
00:11:48,416 --> 00:11:50,627
Buck, should I get it?

97
00:11:50,752 --> 00:11:52,670
Yeah, you have to.

98
00:11:58,426 --> 00:12:00,136
Hello?

99
00:12:00,261 --> 00:12:02,138
Yes, General Turgidson is here...

100
00:12:02,263 --> 00:12:04,807
...he can't come
to the phone at the moment.

101
00:12:04,933 --> 00:12:07,185
Well, this is his secretary,
Miss Scott.

102
00:12:08,311 --> 00:12:10,480
Freddie, how are you?

103
00:12:10,605 --> 00:12:12,815
Fine, and you?

104
00:12:12,941 --> 00:12:17,111
Oh, we were just catching up
on some of the general's paperwork.

105
00:12:17,654 --> 00:12:20,365
Well, look, Freddie, he's tied up
at the moment.

106
00:12:20,490 --> 00:12:23,368
I'm afraid
he can't come to the phone.

107
00:12:23,493 --> 00:12:24,786
Just a minute.

108
00:12:24,911 --> 00:12:28,122
General Turgidson,
a Colonel Puntrich calling.

109
00:12:28,248 --> 00:12:30,124
Tell him to call back.

110
00:12:30,249 --> 00:12:34,879
Freddie, the general says could you
call back in a minute or two?

111
00:12:35,004 --> 00:12:36,881
He says it can't wait.

112
00:12:37,006 --> 00:12:40,301
For Pete's--
Find out what he wants.

113
00:12:40,426 --> 00:12:44,222
Freddie, the thing is, the general
is in the powder room right now.

114
00:12:44,389 --> 00:12:46,683
Could you tell me what it's about?

115
00:12:47,850 --> 00:12:48,893
Just a second.

116
00:12:49,018 --> 00:12:52,188
Apparently they monitored
a transmission eight minutes ago...

117
00:12:52,313 --> 00:12:55,233
...from Burpelson Air Force Base.

118
00:12:56,526 --> 00:13:01,698
Right. It was directed to the
843rd bomb wing on airborne alert.

119
00:13:03,408 --> 00:13:06,869
It decoded as wing attack Plan R.

120
00:13:06,995 --> 00:13:12,500
Well, tell him to call what's-his-name,
the base commander. Ripper.

121
00:13:12,625 --> 00:13:14,335
Do I have to think of everything?

122
00:13:14,460 --> 00:13:19,007
The general suggests you call General
Ripper, the 843rd base commander.

123
00:13:20,049 --> 00:13:22,427
All communications are dead.

124
00:13:22,552 --> 00:13:25,930
Bull! Tell him to do it himself.

125
00:13:26,055 --> 00:13:30,518
Freddie, the general asks if
you could possibly try again yourself.

126
00:13:31,060 --> 00:13:35,690
I see. He says he's tried personally
several times, but everything is dead.

127
00:13:35,815 --> 00:13:39,235
Even the normal phone lines
are shut down.

128
00:13:45,825 --> 00:13:48,703
Fred? Buck. What's it look like?

129
00:13:50,246 --> 00:13:51,748
Yeah?

130
00:13:53,082 --> 00:13:56,127
Well, are you sure it's Plan R?

131
00:13:58,212 --> 00:14:02,967
What's cooking on the threat board?
Nothing? Nothing at all?

132
00:14:05,094 --> 00:14:07,638
I don't like the look of this, Fred.

133
00:14:08,598 --> 00:14:11,100
Tell you what you better do,
old buddy.

134
00:14:11,225 --> 00:14:14,645
Give Elmo and Charlie a blast.
Bump everything up to condition red.

135
00:14:14,771 --> 00:14:17,106
Stand by the blower.
I'll get back to you.

136
00:14:17,231 --> 00:14:19,442
-What's up?
-Nothing, nothing.

137
00:14:20,985 --> 00:14:24,280
-Where's my shorts?
-On the floor. Where are you going?

138
00:14:24,405 --> 00:14:26,115
No place.

139
00:14:26,240 --> 00:14:30,912
I thought I might mosey over to the
war room, see what's doing over there.

140
00:14:31,037 --> 00:14:32,789
It's 3:00 in the morning.

141
00:14:32,914 --> 00:14:34,791
The Air Force never sleeps.

142
00:14:34,916 --> 00:14:38,836
Buck, honey, I'm not sleepy either.

143
00:14:41,464 --> 00:14:44,258
I know how it is, baby.

144
00:14:44,383 --> 00:14:46,427
Tell you what you do.

145
00:14:47,428 --> 00:14:51,349
You just start your countdown
and old Bucky will be back here...

146
00:14:51,474 --> 00:14:55,061
...before you can say, "Blastoff!"

147
00:14:56,270 --> 00:15:01,359
Your Commie has no regard
for human life, not even his own.

148
00:15:01,526 --> 00:15:04,487
And for this reason, men,
I want to impress upon you...

149
00:15:04,612 --> 00:15:07,448
...the need
for extreme watchfulness.

150
00:15:07,573 --> 00:15:11,661
The enemy may come individually
or he may come in strength.

151
00:15:11,786 --> 00:15:14,497
He may even come in the uniform
of our own troops.

152
00:15:15,289 --> 00:15:17,875
But however he comes,
we must stop him.

153
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:21,796
We must not allow him
to gain entrance to this base.

154
00:15:22,296 --> 00:15:26,175
Now, I am going to give you
three simple rules.

155
00:15:26,300 --> 00:15:30,721
First: trust no one,
whatever his uniform or rank...

156
00:15:30,847 --> 00:15:33,349
...unless he is known
to you personally.

157
00:15:33,474 --> 00:15:36,227
Second: anyone or anything...

158
00:15:36,352 --> 00:15:41,232
...that approaches within 200 yards
of the perimeter is to be fired upon.

159
00:15:41,357 --> 00:15:46,904
Third: if in doubt, shoot first
and ask questions afterwards.

160
00:15:47,071 --> 00:15:50,366
I would sooner accept
a few casualties through accident...

161
00:15:50,491 --> 00:15:54,579
...than lose the entire base and
its personnel through carelessness.

162
00:15:54,704 --> 00:15:59,333
Any variation on these rules
must come from me personally.

163
00:15:59,876 --> 00:16:02,712
Now, men, in conclusion...

164
00:16:02,837 --> 00:16:06,841
...I would like to say
that in the two years...

165
00:16:06,966 --> 00:16:10,720
...It has been my privilege
to be your commanding officer...

166
00:16:10,845 --> 00:16:13,723
...I have always expected
the best from you...

167
00:16:13,848 --> 00:16:17,685
...and you have never given me
anything less than that.

168
00:16:17,810 --> 00:16:21,939
Today the nation is counting on us.

169
00:16:22,190 --> 00:16:25,026
We are not going to let them down.

170
00:16:25,151 --> 00:16:27,236
Good luck to you all.

171
00:16:57,767 --> 00:17:00,436
Here's the attack profile, sir.

172
00:17:27,755 --> 00:17:30,258
This is your attack profile.

173
00:17:30,383 --> 00:17:33,594
"To ensure that the enemy cannot
monitor voice transmission...

174
00:17:33,719 --> 00:17:35,805
...or plant false transmission...

175
00:17:35,930 --> 00:17:40,977
...the CRM 114 is to be switched
into all receiver circuits.

176
00:17:41,102 --> 00:17:44,522
The emergency base code prefix
is to be set...

177
00:17:44,647 --> 00:17:46,983
...on the dials of the CRM.

178
00:17:47,108 --> 00:17:51,654
This will block any transmission other
than those preceded by a code prefix.

179
00:17:53,239 --> 00:17:55,366
Stand by to set code prefix.

180
00:17:55,491 --> 00:17:57,868
Roger. Ready to set code prefix.

181
00:17:57,994 --> 00:17:59,495
Set code prefix.

182
00:18:09,505 --> 00:18:12,633
-Code prefix set.
-Lock code prefix.

183
00:18:15,261 --> 00:18:16,679
Code prefix locked.

184
00:18:16,804 --> 00:18:20,308
Switch all receiver circuits
to CRM discriminators.

185
00:18:21,809 --> 00:18:24,687
All circuits switched
to CRM discriminators.

186
00:18:24,812 --> 00:18:27,398
Check auto-destruct circuits.

187
00:18:29,942 --> 00:18:31,902
Auto-destruct circuits checked.

188
00:18:37,283 --> 00:18:41,662
Primary target:
the ICBM complex at Laputa.

189
00:18:41,787 --> 00:18:48,085
Target reference:
Yankee-Golf-Tango, 360.

190
00:18:48,210 --> 00:18:54,258
Thirty-megatonne nuclear device
fused for airburst at 10,000 feet.

191
00:18:54,383 --> 00:18:58,846
Twenty-megatonne nuclear device
will be used if first malfunctions.

192
00:18:58,971 --> 00:19:01,557
Otherwise, proceed
to secondary target:

193
00:19:01,682 --> 00:19:05,686
Missile complex seven miles east
of Borchov.

194
00:19:05,811 --> 00:19:09,732
Target reference:
November-Bravo-X-ray...

195
00:19:09,857 --> 00:19:12,234
...108.

196
00:19:12,360 --> 00:19:17,698
Fused airburst at 10--
Check, 12,000 feet.

197
00:19:28,918 --> 00:19:32,797
Excuse me, sir. Something rather
interesting has just cropped up.

198
00:19:32,922 --> 00:19:35,800
Listen to that. Music.
Civilian broadcasting.

199
00:19:37,218 --> 00:19:41,597
I think the Pentagon has given us
an exercise to test our readiness.

200
00:19:41,722 --> 00:19:43,599
I think it's taking things too far.

201
00:19:43,724 --> 00:19:46,936
Our fellows will be inside Russian
radar cover in 20 minutes.

202
00:19:47,061 --> 00:19:50,606
Listen to that. Chock-a-block
full of stations, all churning it out.

203
00:19:51,899 --> 00:19:53,609
-Mandrake?
-Yes, sir?

204
00:19:53,734 --> 00:19:56,946
I thought I issued instructions
for all radios to be impounded.

205
00:19:57,071 --> 00:20:01,325
You did, and I was in the process of
impounding this when I switched it on.

206
00:20:01,450 --> 00:20:05,121
I thought, our fellows hitting Russian
radar, dropping all their stuff...

207
00:20:05,246 --> 00:20:09,625
...I'd better tell you. Because if
they do, it'll cause a bit of a stink.

208
00:20:09,750 --> 00:20:13,754
Group captain,
the officer-exchange programme...

209
00:20:13,879 --> 00:20:17,466
...does not give you any special
prerogatives to question my orders.

210
00:20:17,591 --> 00:20:21,762
I realise that, sir, but I thought you'd
be rather pleased to hear the news.

211
00:20:21,887 --> 00:20:24,598
I mean, after all....
Well, let's face it.

212
00:20:24,723 --> 00:20:28,686
We don't want to start a nuclear war
unless we really have to, do we?

213
00:20:29,645 --> 00:20:33,274
Please sit down.
And turn that thing off.

214
00:20:33,399 --> 00:20:34,483
Yes, sir.

215
00:20:34,608 --> 00:20:36,026
What about the planes?

216
00:20:36,152 --> 00:20:39,488
Surely we must issue
the recall code immediately.

217
00:20:39,613 --> 00:20:42,366
Group captain, the planes
are not gonna be recalled.

218
00:20:42,491 --> 00:20:46,036
My attack orders have been issued
and the orders stand.

219
00:20:47,413 --> 00:20:51,542
If you'll excuse me saying so, sir,
that would be, to my way of thinking...

220
00:20:51,667 --> 00:20:53,794
...rather an odd way
of looking at it.

221
00:20:53,919 --> 00:20:56,213
If a Russian attack
was in progress...

222
00:20:56,380 --> 00:21:00,217
...we would certainly not be hearing
civilian broadcasting.

223
00:21:00,384 --> 00:21:03,179
-Are you certain of that?
-I'm absolutely positive.

224
00:21:03,304 --> 00:21:05,556
And what if it is true?

225
00:21:06,140 --> 00:21:09,185
I'm afraid I'm still not with you, sir,
because, I mean....

226
00:21:10,686 --> 00:21:13,022
If a Russian attack
was not in progress...

227
00:21:13,147 --> 00:21:18,360
...then your use of Plan R-- In fact,
your orders to the entire wing....

228
00:21:24,992 --> 00:21:30,247
I would say that there was something
dreadfully wrong somewhere.

229
00:21:31,332 --> 00:21:33,667
Why don't you take it easy,
group captain?

230
00:21:33,793 --> 00:21:36,587
Please make me a drink
of grain alcohol and rainwater...

231
00:21:36,712 --> 00:21:39,256
...and help yourself
to whatever you'd like.

232
00:21:47,973 --> 00:21:52,061
General Ripper, sir, as an officer
in Her Majesty's Air Force...

233
00:21:52,186 --> 00:21:55,397
...it is my clear duty
under the present circumstances...

234
00:21:55,523 --> 00:22:00,110
