236
00:22:10,871 --> 00:22:13,541
Sir, I must ask you for the key
and the recall code.

237
00:22:13,666 --> 00:22:15,751
Have you got them handy?

238
00:22:15,876 --> 00:22:18,295
I told you to take it easy,
group captain.

239
00:22:18,420 --> 00:22:20,923
There's nothing anybody can do
about this now.

240
00:22:21,048 --> 00:22:23,425
I'm the only person who knows
the code group.

241
00:22:23,551 --> 00:22:26,720
Then I must insist, sir,
that you give them to me!

242
00:22:35,187 --> 00:22:39,233
Do I take it, sir, you are threatening
a brother officer with a gun?

243
00:22:40,442 --> 00:22:45,573
Mandrake, I suppose
it never occurred to you...

244
00:22:45,698 --> 00:22:49,243
...that while we're chatting here
So enjoyably...

245
00:22:49,368 --> 00:22:53,163
...a decision is being made
by the president...

246
00:22:53,289 --> 00:22:56,458
...and the joint chiefs in the war room
at the Pentagon.

247
00:22:57,501 --> 00:23:03,090
And when they realise there is
no possibility of recalling the wing...

248
00:23:03,215 --> 00:23:06,594
...there will be only one course
of action open:

249
00:23:07,428 --> 00:23:09,471
Total commitment.

250
00:23:11,724 --> 00:23:17,187
Mandrake, do you recall what
Clemenceau once said about war?

251
00:23:17,438 --> 00:23:20,190
No, I don't think I do, sir. No.

252
00:23:21,817 --> 00:23:24,862
He said war was too important
to be left to the generals.

253
00:23:25,946 --> 00:23:29,867
When he said that, 50 years ago...

254
00:23:29,992 --> 00:23:32,536
...he might have been right.

255
00:23:32,661 --> 00:23:34,997
But today...

256
00:23:35,122 --> 00:23:38,500
...war is too important
to be left to politicians.

257
00:23:38,626 --> 00:23:43,047
They have neither the time,
the training...

258
00:23:43,172 --> 00:23:46,216
...nor the inclination
for strategic thought.

259
00:23:49,845 --> 00:23:53,349
I can no longer sit back
and allow...

260
00:23:53,474 --> 00:23:58,562
...Communist infiltration,
Communist indoctrination...

261
00:23:58,687 --> 00:24:01,148
...Communist subversion...

262
00:24:01,774 --> 00:24:05,569
...and the international
Communist conspiracy...

263
00:24:05,694 --> 00:24:08,530
...to sap and impuirify...

264
00:24:08,656 --> 00:24:12,034
...all of our precious bodily fluids.

265
00:24:18,165 --> 00:24:19,541
Staines, is everybody here?

266
00:24:19,667 --> 00:24:22,336
Mr President, the secretary of state
is in Vietnam.

267
00:24:22,461 --> 00:24:26,256
The secretary of defence is in Laos,
the vice president is in Mexico City.

268
00:24:26,382 --> 00:24:29,343
We can establish contact with them
at any time.

269
00:24:29,468 --> 00:24:31,261
The undersecretaries are all here.

270
00:24:31,387 --> 00:24:34,515
Right. Now, General Turgidson,
what's going on here?

271
00:24:36,016 --> 00:24:38,560
Mr President...

272
00:24:38,686 --> 00:24:42,272
...about 35 minutes ago...

273
00:24:42,398 --> 00:24:46,360
...General Jack Ripper,
the commanding general...

274
00:24:46,485 --> 00:24:48,862
...of Burpelson Air Force Base...

275
00:24:48,988 --> 00:24:52,199
...Issued an order to the 34 B-52s
of his wing...

276
00:24:52,324 --> 00:24:54,410
...which were airborne
at the time...

277
00:24:54,535 --> 00:24:58,580
...as part of a special exercise we were
holding called Operation Dropkick.

278
00:24:58,747 --> 00:25:03,419
Now, it appears that the order
called for the planes...

279
00:25:03,544 --> 00:25:06,880
...to attack their targets
inside Russia.

280
00:25:07,006 --> 00:25:11,135
The planes are fully armed
with nuclear weapons...

281
00:25:11,260 --> 00:25:14,763
...with an average load
of 40 megatonnes each.

282
00:25:14,888 --> 00:25:19,393
Now, the central display of Russia will
indicate the position of the planes.

283
00:25:20,644 --> 00:25:23,981
The triangles
are their primary targets.

284
00:25:24,148 --> 00:25:27,985
The squares
are their secondary targets.

285
00:25:28,110 --> 00:25:33,449
The aircraft will begin penetrating
Russian radar cover within 25 minutes.

286
00:25:35,451 --> 00:25:38,746
General Turgidson, I find this
very difficult to understand.

287
00:25:38,871 --> 00:25:41,749
I was under the impression
I was the only one in authority...

288
00:25:41,874 --> 00:25:44,293
...to order the use of
nuclear weapons.

289
00:25:45,419 --> 00:25:49,465
That's right, sir. You are
the only person authorised to do so.

290
00:25:49,590 --> 00:25:53,844
And although I hate to judge
before all the facts are in...

291
00:25:53,969 --> 00:25:57,514
...it's beginning to look like
General Ripper exceeded his authority.

292
00:25:57,681 --> 00:26:02,478
It certainly does. Far beyond the point
I would have imagined possible.

293
00:26:02,603 --> 00:26:06,190
Well, perhaps you're forgetting
the provisions of Plan R, sir.

294
00:26:06,607 --> 00:26:08,150
Plan R?

295
00:26:09,485 --> 00:26:12,988
Plan R is an emergency war plan...

296
00:26:13,113 --> 00:26:15,657
...In which a lower-echelon
commander may order...

297
00:26:15,783 --> 00:26:18,869
...nuclear retaliation
after a sneak attack...

298
00:26:18,994 --> 00:26:22,456
...if the normal chain of command
has been disrupted.

299
00:26:22,581 --> 00:26:25,501
You approved it, sir.
You must remember.

300
00:26:26,960 --> 00:26:30,172
Surely you must recall, sir,
when Senator Beaufort...

301
00:26:30,297 --> 00:26:33,842
...made that big hassle about
our deterrent lacking credibility.

302
00:26:33,967 --> 00:26:38,639
The idea was for Plan R to be
a sort of retaliatory safeguard.

303
00:26:38,764 --> 00:26:40,682
A safeguard?

304
00:26:40,808 --> 00:26:44,019
I admit the human element
seems to have failed us here.

305
00:26:44,144 --> 00:26:47,481
But the idea was to discourage
the Russkies from any hope...

306
00:26:47,606 --> 00:26:50,067
...they could knock out Washington,
and yourself...

307
00:26:50,192 --> 00:26:52,194
...as part of a sneak attack...

308
00:26:52,319 --> 00:26:56,406
...and escape retaliation because of
lack of proper command and control.

309
00:26:56,532 --> 00:26:59,201
I assume the planes will return
automatically...

310
00:26:59,326 --> 00:27:02,079
...once they reach their
fail-safe points.

311
00:27:02,287 --> 00:27:06,917
No, sir, I'm afraid not. The planes
were holding at their fail-safe points...

312
00:27:07,042 --> 00:27:08,710
...when the go code was issued.

313
00:27:08,836 --> 00:27:13,048
Once they fly beyond fail-safe, they do
not require a second order to proceed.

314
00:27:13,173 --> 00:27:15,592
They will continue
until they reach their target.

315
00:27:15,759 --> 00:27:19,888
Then why haven't you radioed the
planes, countermanding the go code?

316
00:27:20,138 --> 00:27:23,433
I'm afraid we're unable to
communicate with any of the aircraft.

317
00:27:23,559 --> 00:27:25,185
Why?

318
00:27:25,853 --> 00:27:28,230
As you may recall, sir...

319
00:27:28,355 --> 00:27:31,900
...one of the provisions
of Plan R provides...

320
00:27:32,025 --> 00:27:36,572
...that once the go code
is received...

321
00:27:36,697 --> 00:27:39,950
...the normal SSB radios
in the aircraft...

322
00:27:40,075 --> 00:27:42,536
...are switched into
a special coded device...

323
00:27:42,661 --> 00:27:45,455
...which I believe is designated
as CRM 114.

324
00:27:45,581 --> 00:27:47,624
Now, in order
to prevent the enemy...

325
00:27:47,749 --> 00:27:50,127
...from issuing fake
or confusing orders...

326
00:27:50,294 --> 00:27:54,131
...CRM 114 is designed
not to receive at all...

327
00:27:54,298 --> 00:27:56,550
...unless the message is preceded...

328
00:27:56,675 --> 00:27:59,761
...by the correct three-letter
code group prefix.

329
00:27:59,887 --> 00:28:05,142
Do you mean to tell me, general, you
will be unable to recall the aircraft?

330
00:28:05,309 --> 00:28:08,228
That's the size of it.
However, we are ploughing through...

331
00:28:08,353 --> 00:28:11,148
...every possible three-letter
combination of the code.

332
00:28:11,315 --> 00:28:16,445
But since there are
17,000 permutations...

333
00:28:16,570 --> 00:28:20,115
...it's going to take us about two days
to transmit them all.

334
00:28:20,240 --> 00:28:22,951
How soon will planes penetrate
Russian radar cover?

335
00:28:23,076 --> 00:28:26,496
-Eighteen minutes from now.
-Are you in contact with Ripper?

336
00:28:26,622 --> 00:28:31,460
No, sir. General Ripper sealed off
the base and cut off communications.

337
00:28:31,585 --> 00:28:34,796
-Where did you get this information?
-General Ripper called...

338
00:28:34,922 --> 00:28:39,468
...Strategic Air Command headquarters
shortly after he issued the go code.

339
00:28:39,593 --> 00:28:43,013
I have a portion of the transcript,
if you'd like me to read it.

340
00:28:43,138 --> 00:28:45,098
Read it.

341
00:28:46,850 --> 00:28:49,436
The duty officer asked
General Ripper...

342
00:28:49,561 --> 00:28:53,649
...to confirm the fact that he had
issued the go code and he said:

343
00:28:53,774 --> 00:28:58,195
"Yes, gentlemen, they are on their way
in and no one can bring them back.

344
00:28:58,570 --> 00:29:01,114
For the sake of our country
and our way of life...

345
00:29:01,240 --> 00:29:03,825
...I suggest you get the rest of SAC
in after them.

346
00:29:03,951 --> 00:29:08,830
Otherwise, we will be totally destroyed
by Red retaliation.

347
00:29:08,956 --> 00:29:14,211
My boys will give you the best kind
of start: 1400 megatonnes' worth.

348
00:29:14,336 --> 00:29:17,839
And you sure as hell
won't stop them now.

349
00:29:17,965 --> 00:29:20,801
So let's get going.
There's no other choice.

350
00:29:20,926 --> 00:29:25,722
God willing, we will prevail
in peace and freedom from fear...

351
00:29:25,847 --> 00:29:29,184
...and in true health
through the purity...

352
00:29:29,309 --> 00:29:33,146
...and essence of our natural...

353
00:29:33,271 --> 00:29:34,690
...fluids.

354
00:29:35,649 --> 00:29:37,693
God bless you all.”

355
00:29:39,611 --> 00:29:41,405
Then he hung up.

356
00:29:42,322 --> 00:29:45,867
We're still trying to figure out
the meaning of that last phrase.

357
00:29:45,993 --> 00:29:50,247
There's nothing to figure out.
This man is obviously a psychotic.

358
00:29:50,414 --> 00:29:55,419
I'd like to hold off judgement on a thing
like that, sir, until all the facts are in.

359
00:29:55,544 --> 00:30:00,090
General Turgidson, when you
instituted the human reliability tests...

360
00:30:00,215 --> 00:30:02,592
...you assured me there was
no possibility...

361
00:30:02,718 --> 00:30:05,095
...of such a thing ever occurring.

362
00:30:06,138 --> 00:30:10,183
Well, I don't think it's quite fair
to condemn the whole programme...

363
00:30:10,309 --> 00:30:12,894
...because of a single slip-up, sir.

364
00:30:13,020 --> 00:30:15,522
I wanna speak to General Ripper
on the telephone.

365
00:30:15,647 --> 00:30:17,107
I'm afraid that's impossible.

366
00:30:17,441 --> 00:30:21,069
General Turgidson, I am becoming
less and less interested...

367
00:30:21,194 --> 00:30:24,781
...in your estimates
of what is possible and impossible.

368
00:30:25,907 --> 00:30:28,285
-General Faceman.
-Yes, sir?

369
00:30:28,452 --> 00:30:30,954
Are there any Army units
stationed near Burpelson?

370
00:30:31,079 --> 00:30:33,206
I'll just check, sir.

371
00:30:37,711 --> 00:30:39,463
Hello?

372
00:30:41,006 --> 00:30:44,259
I told you never to call me here.
Don't you know where I am?

373
00:30:46,386 --> 00:30:49,264
Look, baby, I can't talk to you now.

374
00:30:49,389 --> 00:30:51,933
My president needs me.

375
00:30:52,059 --> 00:30:55,645
Of course Bucky would rather
be there with you.

376
00:30:56,730 --> 00:30:59,816
Of course it isn't only physical.

377
00:30:59,983 --> 00:31:02,402
I deeply respect you
as a human being.

378
00:31:02,527 --> 00:31:05,614
Someday I'm gonna make you
Mrs. Buck Turgidson.

379
00:31:06,740 --> 00:31:09,659
Oh, listen, you go back to sleep.

380
00:31:09,785 --> 00:31:12,662
Bucky will be back there
just as soon as he can.

381
00:31:12,788 --> 00:31:17,459
All right. Listen, sug,
don't forget to say your prayers.

382
00:31:24,424 --> 00:31:28,303
Apparently,
the 23rd Airborne Division...

383
00:31:28,428 --> 00:31:31,181
...Is stationed seven miles away
at Alvarado.

384
00:31:31,306 --> 00:31:35,519
General Faceman, I want them to enter
the base, locate General Ripper...

385
00:31:35,644 --> 00:31:37,979
...and put him
in immediate contact with me.

386
00:31:38,105 --> 00:31:39,689
Yes, sir.

387
00:31:39,815 --> 00:31:42,859
Mr President, if I may advise.

388
00:31:42,984 --> 00:31:47,447
Under a condition red, it is standard
procedure the base be sealed off...

389
00:31:47,572 --> 00:31:50,283
...and the base defended
by base security troops.

390
00:31:50,408 --> 00:31:54,788
Any force trying to enter there would
certainly encounter heavy casualties.

391
00:31:54,913 --> 00:31:58,708
General Turgidson, with all due
respect for your defence team...

392
00:31:58,834 --> 00:32:01,711
...my boys can brush them aside
without too much trouble.

393
00:32:02,671 --> 00:32:07,425
Mr President, there are one or two
points I'd like to make, if I may?

394
00:32:08,468 --> 00:32:09,886
Go ahead, general.

395
00:32:11,430 --> 00:32:16,059
One: our hopes for recalling
the 843rd bomb wing...

396
00:32:16,184 --> 00:32:20,397
...are quickly being reduced
to a very low order of probability.

397
00:32:20,564 --> 00:32:23,358
Two: in less than 15 minutes
from now...

398
00:32:23,483 --> 00:32:26,570
...the Russkies will be making
radar contact with the planes.

399
00:32:26,695 --> 00:32:28,697
Three: when they do...

400
00:32:28,822 --> 00:32:32,367
...they will go absolutely ape and
strike back with everything they've got.

401
00:32:32,826 --> 00:32:36,371
Four: if, prior to this time...

402
00:32:36,496 --> 00:32:40,000
...we have done nothing to suppress
their retaliatory capabilities...

403
00:32:40,125 --> 00:32:42,711
...we will suffer virtual annihilation.

404
00:32:42,836 --> 00:32:44,754
Now...

405
00:32:46,464 --> 00:32:48,758
five:

406
00:32:48,884 --> 00:32:51,428
If, on the other hand...

407
00:32:53,221 --> 00:32:58,185
...we immediately launched an attack
on their airfields and missile bases...

408
00:32:58,310 --> 00:33:01,730
...we'd stand a good chance of
catching them with their pants down.

409
00:33:01,855 --> 00:33:04,065
We've got a 5-to-1
missile superiority.

410
00:33:04,191 --> 00:33:07,110
We could easily assign three missiles
to every target...

411
00:33:07,235 --> 00:33:10,906
...and still have an effective reserve
force for any other contingency.

412
00:33:11,031 --> 00:33:16,036
Six: an unofficial study which
we undertook of this eventuality...

413
00:33:16,161 --> 00:33:21,041
...indicated that we would destroy
90 percent of their nuclear capabilities.

414
00:33:21,166 --> 00:33:23,251
We would therefore prevail...

415
00:33:23,376 --> 00:33:27,422
...and suffer only modest civilian
casualties from their remaining force...

416
00:33:27,464 --> 00:33:30,967
...which would be badly damaged
and uncoordinated.

417
00:33:31,134 --> 00:33:34,304
General, it is the avowed policy
of our country...

418
00:33:34,429 --> 00:33:36,765
...never to strike first
with nuclear weapons.

419
00:33:36,890 --> 00:33:41,561
Well, Mr President, I'd say Ripper
has already invalidated that policy.

420
00:33:41,686 --> 00:33:46,107
That was not an act of national policy.
There are still alternatives open to us.

421
00:33:47,067 --> 00:33:48,818
Mr President...

422
00:33:49,736 --> 00:33:52,113
...we are rapidly approaching
a moment of truth...

423
00:33:52,239 --> 00:33:55,116
...both for ourselves
and for the life of our nation.

424
00:33:55,242 --> 00:33:57,827
Now, truth is not always
a pleasant thing.

425
00:33:57,953 --> 00:34:00,455
But it is necessary now
to make a choice.

426
00:34:00,580 --> 00:34:03,291
To choose between two
admittedly regrettable...

427
00:34:03,416 --> 00:34:06,836
...but nevertheless distinguishable,
postwar environments.

428
00:34:06,962 --> 00:34:09,005
One where 20 million people
are Killed.

429
00:34:09,130 --> 00:34:11,675
The other, 150 million people killed.

430
00:34:11,800 --> 00:34:14,761
You're talking about mass murder,
general, not war.

431
00:34:14,886 --> 00:34:18,431
Mr President, I'm not saying
we wouldn't get our hair mussed.

432
00:34:18,556 --> 00:34:23,144
But I do say no more than
10 to 20 million killed, tops.

433
00:34:23,270 --> 00:34:25,188
Depending on the breaks.

434
00:34:25,313 --> 00:34:29,276
I will not go down in history as the
greatest mass murderer since Hitler.

435
00:34:29,401 --> 00:34:31,820
It might be better
if you were more concerned...

436
00:34:31,945 --> 00:34:35,323
...with the American people than
with your image in history books.

437
00:34:35,448 --> 00:34:38,451
General Turgidson, I've heard
quite sufficient from you.

438
00:34:38,576 --> 00:34:40,370
Thank you very much.

439
00:34:40,996 --> 00:34:43,540
Mr President, they have
the ambassador upstairs.

440
00:34:43,665 --> 00:34:47,210
-Oh, good. Any difficulty?
