Have him brought here.

442
00:34:49,921 --> 00:34:51,381
Yes, sir.

443
00:34:51,506 --> 00:34:54,009
Is that the Russian ambassador?

444
00:34:54,134 --> 00:34:56,177
Yes, it is, general.

445
00:34:58,305 --> 00:35:01,182
Am I to understand
the Russian ambassador...

446
00:35:01,308 --> 00:35:03,685
...Is to be admitted entrance
to the war room?

447
00:35:03,810 --> 00:35:06,688
That is correct.
He is here on my orders.

448
00:35:09,524 --> 00:35:11,818
I don't know exactly how
to put this, sir...

449
00:35:11,943 --> 00:35:15,238
...but are you aware of what
a breach of security that would be?

450
00:35:15,363 --> 00:35:19,534
I mean, he'll see everything.
He'll see the big board.

451
00:35:20,452 --> 00:35:25,081
That is precisely the idea, general.
That is precisely the idea.

452
00:35:26,625 --> 00:35:30,545
Staines, get Premier Kissoff
on the hot line.

453
00:35:38,011 --> 00:35:41,556
Survival kit contents check.

454
00:35:41,681 --> 00:35:46,436
In them, you will find
one .45-calibre automatic...

455
00:35:46,561 --> 00:35:49,064
...two boxes of ammunition...

456
00:35:49,189 --> 00:35:52,525
...four days' concentrated
emergency rations...

457
00:35:52,901 --> 00:35:55,862
...one drug issue
containing antibiotics...

458
00:35:55,987 --> 00:36:00,325
...morphine, vitamin pills,
pep pills...

459
00:36:00,700 --> 00:36:04,204
...Sleeping pills,
tranquilizer pills...

460
00:36:04,579 --> 00:36:09,084
One miniature combination
Russian phrase book and Bible...

461
00:36:09,501 --> 00:36:12,087
